<p>All in all, i like the concept and the flow, the last dialog is what felt the least natural, if that makes sense, here are the thoughts that i got as i read the piece:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Bullet-pointed&nbsp;critique</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Bullet-pointed&nbsp;critique</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li>Who are the entrants? (Answered later in the article, but felt kinda lost about their purpose/identity until it was answered, not sure how i'd tell you to fix this, or if it needs fixing, but felt it was important enough to mention)</li>
<li>The text looks like hebraic symbols, is that intended to be a easter egg or a connection to something or another?</li>
<li>&quot;currently unidentified runes&quot; isn't there a more 'clinical' term for that? Something along thaumaturgical anomalous symbols or something, grain of salt here, i'm still grasping that whole clinical terminology aspect</li>
<li>&quot;Because you boarded up the last one, jackass&#8230;&quot; Could change jackass to (expletive) but that's a nitpick i guess</li>
<li>Containment Log 1D: You're repeating information from the containment attempt on the foreword, i think it isn't necessary. Specifically, &quot;Attempt at convicing the employees to relocate SCP-XXXX-1&quot;</li>
<li>Also, if it's invisible to some and visible to others, how does that translate to recorded media? Do the rules still apply? The footage description implies that anyone can see it when recorded, which if true, means you could have an AR setup to look for them with VR googles and a camera, and if that's the case, does that imply people recording random things with cameras/cellphones could see them when they shouldn't?</li>
<li>&quot;SCP-XXXX-1B: Dude, we found that one like two seconds after finding yours. Much better place to be honest. We’ve traded on the London Stock Exchange there.&quot; Does that mean the unveiled earth is better for them? It felt that way from this line.</li>
<li>Containment Log 1E, the containment attempt part is empty, unless that's on purpose, but it looks like a typo.</li>
<li>&quot;to help you make your decision, but in 24, hours&quot; &lt; That last comma is a typo i think</li>
<li>I understand the meaning behind the punchline, but with the infodump on the last dialog, it feels like you're hitting the point a smidge too much. It can work either way, however.</li>
<li>Moreover, the timejump between negotiation and figuring out the choice feels &quot;rushed&quot;, as if they managed to find it by means of epiphany. I think it would help to clarify how they got to this specific solution, maybe the Wandsmen have had this happen before, and had a similar setup? Something along that. I can understand how they'd have reached that particular solution however, so if you want to keep it for the sake of brevity, i could understand that reasoning.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>

