<h1><span>Edits/SPaG/Whatever</span></h1>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX-1 is to be staffed at all times by Foundation personnel, with at least one taking on the role of a concierge.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>the word staffed here is a bit weird, but I'm unsure what you would replace this with.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>No entrants are to be permitted to leave.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;No entrants are permitted to leave.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The use of amnestics on entrants is strictly forbidden.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;The use of amnestics on entrants is strictly prohibited&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>It is only visible to individuals who have been granted access to SCP-XXXX-1; those with access to SCP-XXXX have been estimated to comprise of 20% of the population.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Are you talking about the two different things? Like SCP-XXXX-1 vs SCP-XXXX?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX’s location varies, although it is consistently found on flat surfaces in locations with low amounts of human activity. Examples include:</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Those examples include places with a lot of human activity. Floors, Back Alleys, cardboard boxes are normally where people are.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Individuals who can see SCP-XXXX are granted access to SCP-XXXX-1; access to SCP-XXXX-1 is done by cupping a hand over SCP-XXXX as well as on the surface on which it is located.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;Individuals who can see SCP-XXXX are granted access to SCP-XXXX-1. Access to SCP-XXXX-1 is done by cupping a hand over SCP-XXXX as well as on the surface it is located.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>How this information was obtained is currently unknown.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;It is currently unknown how this information was obtained.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-XXXX-1A and SCP-XXXX-1B are bipedal avian creatures with features similar to owls (Strigiformes) and both standing at approximately 2 meters.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;SCP-XXXX-1A and SCP-XXXX-1B are bipedal avian creatures with features similar to owls (Strigiformes) and standing at approximately 2 meters.&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>//&lt;Meyers slings her rifle over her shoulder.&gt;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Missing ending //</p>
<blockquote>
<p>After 24 hours you will default to the Handcuffs.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>But isn't it the canteen in the Specials containment procedures?</p>
<hr />
<h1><span>final notes</span></h1>
<p>Hmm, this is alright. I dislike how the addendum was structured. I would have broken them into separate addendums, though I think that's a bit more of a nit pick. I dislike the explanation of the handcuff object, it just seems really cheesy and just weird in context.</p>
<p>Other than that, I did enjoy this and I think y'all have done good with this. Though, I do suggest getting more critique before posting.</p>
<p>Good luck!</p>
